NAME		mount  --  mount file system
.sp
.ti 0
SYNOPSIS	mount_____ special dir
.sp
.ti 0
DESCRIPTION	mount_____
announces to the system that a removable file system
has been mounted on the device
corresponding to special
file special_______.
Directory dir___ (which must exist already)
becomes the name of the root of the newly mounted
file system.
.sp
.ti 0
FILES		--
.sp
.ti 0
SEE ALSO	umount
.sp
.ti 0
DIAGNOSTICS	"?",
if the special file is already in use, cannot be read,
or if dir___ does not exist.
.sp
.ti 0
BUGS		Should be usable only by the super-user.
.sp
